bit_field.name: CYCCNTENA
bit_field.description: CYCCNTENA bit. Enables CYCCNT. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: POSTPRESET
bit_field.description: POSTPRESET bits. Reload value for the POSTCNT counter. This field is UNK/SBZP if the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: POSTINIT
bit_field.description: POSTINIT bits. Initial value for the POSTCNT counter. This field is UNK/SBZP if the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: CYCTAP
bit_field.description: CYCTAP bit. Selects the position of the POSTCNT tap on the CYCCNT counter. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: SYNCTAP
bit_field.description: SYNCTAP bits. Selects the position of the synchronization packet counter tap on the CYCCNT counter. This determines the Synchronization packet rate.

bit_field.name: PCSAMPLENA
bit_field.description: PCSAMPLENA bit. Enables use of POSTCNT counter as a timer for Periodic PC sample packet generation. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOTRCPKT bit is RAO or the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL_PCSAMPLENA_0b0
bit_field_value.description: No Periodic PC sample packets generated.

bit_field.name: EXCTRCENA
bit_field.description: EXCTRCENA bit. Enables generation of exception trace. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOTRCPKT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: CPIEVTENA
bit_field.description: CPIEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the CPI counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: EXCEVTENA
bit_field.description: EXCEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the Exception overhead counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: SLEEPEVTENA
bit_field.description: SLEEPEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the Sleep counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: LSUEVTENA
bit_field.description: LSUEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the LSU counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: FOLDEVTENA
bit_field.description: FOLDEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the Folded-instruction counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field.name: CYCEVTENA
bit_field.description: CYCEVTENA bit. Enables POSTCNT underflow Event counter packets generation. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOTRCPKT bit is RAO or the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL_CYCEVTENA_0b1
bit_field_value.description: POSTCNT underflow packets generated, if PCSAMPLENA set to 0.

bit_field.name: NOPFRCNT
bit_field.description: NOPFRCNT bit. Shows whether the implementation supports the profiling counters.

bit_field.name: NOCYCCNT
bit_field.description: NOCYCCNT bit. Shows whether the implementation supports a cycle counter.

bit_field.name: NOEXTTRIG
bit_field.description: NOEXTRRIG bit. Shows whether the implementation includes external match signals, CMPMATCH[N].

bit_field.name: NOTRCPKT
bit_field.description: NOTRCPKT bit. Shows whether the implementation supports trace sampling and exception tracing. If this bit is RAZ, the NOCYCCNT bit must also RAZ.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL_NOTRCPKT_0b0
bit_field_value.description: Trace sampling and exception tracing supported.

bit_field_value.name: CTRL_NOTRCPKT_0b1
bit_field_value.description: Trace sampling and exception tracing not supported.

bit_field.name: NUMCOMP
bit_field.description: NUMCOMP bits. Number of comparators implemented. A value of zero indicates no comparator support.

bit_field.name: CYCCNT
bit_field.description: CYCCNT[31:0]. Incrementing cycle counter value. When enabled, CYCCNT increments on each processor clock cycle. On overflow, CYCCNT wraps to zero.

bit_field.name: CPICNT
bit_field.description: CPICNT[7:0]. The base CPI counter. Counts additional cycles required to execute multi-cycle instructions, except those recorded by DWT_LSUCNT, and counts any instruction fetch stalls.

bit_field.name: EXCCNT
bit_field.description: EXCCNT[7:0]. The exception overhead counter. Counts the total cycles spent in exception processing.

bit_field.name: SLEEPCNT
bit_field.description: SLEEPCNT[7:0]. Sleep counter. Counts the total number of cycles that the processor is sleeping.

bit_field.name: LSUCNT
bit_field.description: LSUCNT[7:0]. Load-store counter. Increments on any additional cycles required to execute load or store instructions.

bit_field.name: FOLDCNT
bit_field.description: FOLDCNT[7:0]. Folded-instruction counter. Increments on each instruction that takes 0 cycles.

bit_field.name: EIASAMPLE
bit_field.description: EIASAMPLE[31:0]. Executed Instruction Address sample value.

bit_field.name: COMP
bit_field.description: COMP[31:0]. Reference value for comparison.

bit_field.name: MASK
bit_field.description: MASK[4:0]. The size of the ignore mask, 0-31 bits, applied to address range matching. The maximum mask size is IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED. A debugger can write 0b11111 to this field and then read the register back to determine the maximum mask size supported.

bit_field.name: FUNCTION
bit_field.description: FUNCTION[3:0]. Selects action taken on comparator match. This field resets to zero.

bit_field.name: EMITRANGE
bit_field.description: EMITRANGE bit. If the implementation supports trace sampling, enables generation of Data trace address offset packets, that hold Daddr[15:0]. If DWT_CTRL.NOTRCPKT is RAZ then this bit is UNK/SBZP.

bit_field_value.name: COMPARATOR_EMITRANGE_0b0
bit_field_value.description: Data trace address offset packets disabled.

bit_field_value.name: COMPARATOR_EMITRANGE_0b1
bit_field_value.description: Enable Data trace address offset packet generation.

bit_field.name: CYCMATCH
bit_field.description: CYCMATCH bit. If the implementation supports cycle counting, enable cycle count comparison for comparator 0. If DWT_CTRL.NOCYCCNT is RAZ then this bit is UNK/SBZP.

bit_field_value.name: COMPARATOR_CYCMATCH_0b1
bit_field_value.description: Compare DWT_COMP0 with the cycle counter, DWT_CYCCNT.

bit_field.name: DATAVMATCH
bit_field.description: DATAVMATCH bit. Enables data value comparison, if supported. For comparator 0, when the CYCMATCH is set to 1, DATAVMATCH must be set to 0 for it to perform cycle count comparison. See LNK1ENA, DATAVSIZE, DATAVADDR0 and DATAVADDR1 for related information. If the implementation does not support data value comparison this bit is RAZ/WI.

bit_field.name: LNK1ENA
bit_field.description: LNK1ENA bit. Indicates whether the implementation supports use of a second linked comparator. When LNK1ENA is RAO, the DATAVADDR1 field specifies the comparator to use as the second linked comparator.

bit_field.name: DATAVSIZE
bit_field.description: DATAVSIZE[1:0]. For data value matching, specifies the size of the required data comparison.

bit_field_value.name: COMPARATOR_DATAVSIZE_0b11
bit_field_value.description: Reserved. Using this value means behaviour is UNPREDICTABLE.

bit_field.name: DATAVADDR0
bit_field.description: DATAVADDR0[3:0]. When the DATAVMATCH bit is set to 1 this field can hold the comparator number of a comparator to use for linked address comparison. The DWT unit ignores the value of this field if the DATAVMATCH bit is set to 0.

bit_field.name: DATAVADDR1
bit_field.description: DATAVADDR1[3:0]. When the DATAVMATCH and LNK1ENA bits are both 1, this field can hold the comparator number of a second comparator to use for linked address comparison. The DWT unit ignores the value of this field unless the LNK1ENA bit is RAO and the DATAVMATCH bit is set to 1. If LNK1ENA is RAZ, this field is RAZ/WI.

bit_field.name: MATCHED
bit_field.description: MATCHED bit. Comparator match. A value of 1 indicates that the operation defined by the FUNCTION field occurred since the last read of the register. Reading the register clears this bit to 0.
